# Plan Execution Loop

> **Thesis:** One plan slice at a time — implement, audit (≥90/100), fix, re-audit — then next slice. Parent agent orchestrates; subagents implement and audit.
>
> **Invoke when:** User says "run the plan", "execute slice X", or points at `docs/plans/*.md` for implementation.

## Per-slice loop (do not skip)

```
1. IMPLEMENT — Task subagent: read plan slice only; implement; run verification commands; update Progress row
2. AUDIT   — Task subagent (readonly): grade /100 vs slice acceptance; PASS only if ≥90
3. FIX     — if FAIL: Task subagent applies audit fix list; no scope creep
4. RE-AUDIT — repeat 2–3 until ≥90
5. NEXT SLICE — only after current slice PASS
```

## Subagent prompts must include

- Exact slice ID and file path to plan section
- Acceptance criteria from plan (copy verbatim)
- Verification commands (`npm run test:coverage`, `check_spec_drift.sh`, etc.)
- Forbidden scope (other slices, unrelated refactors)
- "Return: grade, PASS/FAIL, files changed, blockers"

## Parent agent responsibilities

- Read plan slice before dispatching — do not dump whole plan into subagent
- Run `opt/homebrew/bin/bash scripts/check_spec_drift.sh origin/main` before commit when handler/service touched
- Commit per slice or logical batch after PASS; never commit with audit below 90
- Update `docs/plans/*.md` Progress table after each PASS

## Audit dimensions (default weights)

| Dimension | What to check |
|-----------|---------------|
| Completeness | All deliverables in slice scope |
| Accuracy | Paths, commands, plan citations match repo |
| Acceptance | Slice-specific gates met |
| Scope | No slice creep; spec sync if required |
| Verification | Commands run, exit 0 |

## Contract closeout (from `slice-and-ship`)

Before commit on backend slices: spec sync or `[skip-spec(module): reason]`; run `check_spec_drift.sh`.

## Parallel slices within one plan

Independent slices (e.g. B4a ∥ B4b ∥ B4c) may run as parallel **implement** subagents in the **same working tree** when they touch disjoint files. Each slice still gets its own **audit → fix → re-audit** loop before merge.

Pre-flight: `rg` plan slice file lists — if two slices touch the same file, run them sequentially.

## Multiple plans in parallel (worktrees required)

When running **two or more plans** concurrently (each with its own execution loop), **do not share one working tree.** Each plan gets isolated git state — same rules as `parallel-subagents` "When subagents will commit code".

```
Parent branch (e.g. steve-dev)
├── worktree: ../golid-plan-a  →  branch plan/a-short-name  →  docs/plans/foo.md loop
└── worktree: ../golid-plan-b  →  branch plan/b-short-name  →  docs/plans/bar.md loop
```

**Setup (parent agent):**

```bash
git worktree add -b plan/<name> ../golid-<name> HEAD
# Dispatch plan execution loop subagent with working_directory = that worktree path
```

**Land back on parent branch:**

1. Pre-flight: `rg` both plans for overlapping file paths — resolve or serialize conflicting plans
2. Cherry-pick **one commit at a time** from each plan branch (smaller/additive plan first) — see `parallel-subagents` cherry-pick loop
3. After each pick: build + test; fix conflicts before next pick
4. Run full verification on parent: `check_spec_drift.sh`, `npm run typecheck`, `go test ./...`
5. `git worktree remove` + `git branch -D plan/<name>` when landed

**Forbidden on parent repo while worktrees run:** `git reset --hard`, `git clean -fd`, `git checkout --force` — can destroy uncommitted work in sibling worktrees.

## Anti-patterns

| Bad | Good |
|-----|------|
| Implement B4a–c in one pass | B4a PASS → then B4b |
| Two plans editing same branch simultaneously | One worktree per plan |
| Bulk cherry-pick plan commits | One commit at a time |
| Audit whole plan at end | Audit each slice before next |
| Skip audit because "tests pass" | Audit grades behavior + docs + scope |
| Commit at 82/100 | Fix loop until ≥90 |

